bc-seek (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Promote to stable 1.x alongside the rest of the bc-* ecosystem.
  * Add libFuzzer harness infrastructure under fuzzing/ with harnesses
    for cli_parse (argv through bc_seek_cli_program_spec), filter_parsers
    (--size / --mtime / --type / --perm / --threads values), and
    glob_match (pattern matching with case-insensitive mode).
  * Rebuilt against libbc-core 1.1.0 which carries the
    count_lines_with_pattern shift-by-32 UB fix.
  * No public CLI change.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Wed, 22 Apr 2026 08:00:00 +0000

bc-seek (0.1.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Refactor: consume new public APIs from upstream libs (libbc-io 1.1.0
    dirent_reader, libbc-allocators 1.1.0 typed_array append_bulk,
    libbc-runtime 1.1.0 error_collector). Drops ~200 LOC of duplicated
    internal primitives (bc_seek_dirent, bc_seek_byte_buffer,
    bc_seek_error_collector).
  * No CLI surface change. No behavioural change. Bench on
    /var/benchmarks (953k files, 19 GB, Ryzen 7 5700G, 10 warm runs
    median): 0.181 s, identical to 0.1.0 (0.184 s) — within bench noise.
  * Build-Depends now require libbc-io >= 1.1.0, libbc-allocators >=
    1.1.0, libbc-runtime >= 1.1.0.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 21:50:00 +0000

bc-seek (0.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial public release.
  * Parallel hardware-saturating file search CLI backed by the
    bc-concurrency MPMC-queue + per-worker slot pattern.
  * find(1)-compatible predicates: --name, --iname, --path, --type,
    --size, --mtime, --newer, --perm, --max-depth, --min-depth.
  * Walk-control flags: --hidden, --no-ignore, --follow-symlinks,
    --one-file-system.
  * Output: --output PATH|-, --null/-0 for xargs -0 consumption,
    global --threads auto|0|N.
  * fd(1)-style default prune list for common build / VCS dirs
    (.git, node_modules, target, __pycache__, .venv, .cache, ...).
  * Stat-lazy predicate evaluation: zero stat syscalls unless
    --size / --mtime / --newer / --perm is active.
  * Graceful SIGINT / SIGTERM handling -> exit code 130.
  * On warm-cache /var/benchmarks (~1.07M files, 19 GB, 5700G):
    - walk --type=f: 0.23s (find: 1.60s, fd: 0.26s)
    - name '*.c':    0.21s (find: 1.90s, fd: 0.22s)
    - size +1M:      0.38s (find: 3.10s, fd: 0.62s)

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 20:00:00 +0000
